From 9ef92d7081929b0223089cbaf5d7d15fce0e905a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Volker Badziong <development@richtfest.tech>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 10:46:14 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] Add docker.cgroup_parent to place containers under a
 systemd slice

Adds an opt-in, node-level docker.cgroup_parent configuration key that
sets HostConfig.CgroupParent on every server and installer container
Wings creates. With the systemd cgroup driver this places containers
under a named, admin-managed systemd slice instead of system.slice,
making cgroup v2 resource policy (memory.min/low/high protection floors
and ceilings, cpu.weight, io.weight) applicable to the game workload as
a whole without affecting host services.

The value is validated at Wings startup: it must be a bare unit name
ending in ".slice" with no whitespace, control characters or path
separators. An empty value (the default) leaves Docker's placement
unchanged. Existing containers are not moved; the setting applies to
containers created after the configuration change.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
